classes.label: Walker
description:
Iterates over all nodes in the AST and calls the appropriate visitor
functions.

AST nodes supported:

- [x] command
- [x] option
- [x] mode
- [x] function
- [x] source
- [x] column
- [x] literal
- [x] list literal
- [x] timeInterval
- [x] inlineCast
- [x] unknown

children.label: walk
description: Walks the AST and calls the appropriate visitor functions.

children.label: commands
description: Walks the AST and extracts all command statements.

children.label: node
description: AST node to extract parameters from.

children.label: params
description: Walks the AST and extracts all parameter literals.

children.label: node
description: AST node to extract parameters from.

children.label: find
description: Finds and returns the first node that matches the search criteria.

children.label: node
description: AST node to start the search from.

children.label: predicate
description: A function that returns true if the node matches the search criteria.

returnComment: The first node that matches the search criteria.

children.label: findAll
description: Finds and returns all nodes that match the search criteria.

children.label: node
description: AST node to start the search from.

children.label: predicate
description: A function that returns true if the node matches the search criteria.

returnComment: All nodes that match the search criteria.

children.label: match
description:
Matches a single node against a template object. Returns the first node
that matches the template.

children.label: node
description: AST node to match against the template.

children.label: template
description: Template object to match against the node.

returnComment: The first node that matches the template

children.label: matchAll
description:
Matches all nodes against a template object. Returns all nodes that match
the template.

children.label: node
description: AST node to match against the template.

children.label: template
description: Template object to match against the node.

returnComment: All nodes that match the template

children.label: findFunction
description: Finds the first function that matches the predicate.

children.label: node
description: AST node from which to search for a function

children.label: predicate
description: Callback function to determine if the function is found

returnComment: The first function that matches the predicate

children.label: hasFunction
description: Searches for at least one occurrence of a function or expression in the AST.

children.label: node
description: AST subtree to search in.

children.label: name
description: Function or expression name to search for.

returnComment: True if the function or expression is found in the AST.

children.label: parts
description:
An identifier can be composed of multiple parts, e.g: part1.part2.`part``3️⃣`.
This property contains the parsed unquoted parts of the identifier.
For example: `['part1', 'part2', 'part`3️⃣']`.

children.label: subtype
description: Default is 'variadic-call'.

children.label: cluster
description:
Represents the cluster part of the source identifier. Empty string if not
present.

```
FROM [<cluster>:]<index>
```

children.label: index
description:
Represents the index part of the source identifier. Unescaped and unquoted.

```
FROM [<cluster>:]<index>
```

children.label: visitAny
description: Called for any node type that does not have a specific visitor.

children.label: node
description: Any valid AST node.

misc.label: ESQLAstItem
description:
An array of AST nodes represents different things in different contexts.
For example, in command top level arguments it is treated as an "assignment expression".

misc.label: ESQLSingleAstItem
description: Represents an *expression* in the AST.
